<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3659845>
    dc:description "Figs 47–50. – 47–48. Plusiocampa (Plusiocampa) dublanskii Sendra & Turbanov sp. nov. 47. Specimen from Kizil-Koba (= Krasnaya) Cave, Dolgorukovsky karst massif, Crimean Peninsula (Coll. AS); surface of metanotum, detail. 48. Holotype, ♂, 2.7 mm long, from same locality (ZMMU Dip0006); pretarsus, dorsal view. – 49–50. P. (P.) aff. dublanskii Sendra & Turbanov sp. nov., ♂, 2.8 mm long, from Abrskila Cave, Abkhazia, Western Caucasus (ZMMU). 49. Metathoracic pretarsus. 50. Urosternite I. Scale bars: 49 = 50 μm; 50 = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3659845/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

